Sir William Peel was a British colonial administrator who became the 18th Governor of Hong Kong (1930-1935)

Sir William Peel (Chinese name: 貝璐, 27 February 1875 – 24 February 1945) was a British Colonial administrator who was the 18th Governor of Hong Kong from May 9, 1930 until May 17, 1935.  He also served as Chancellor of the University of Hong Kong from 1930 to 1935.  (sample text info from Wikipedia and HKU lib)
